Notify Applicants of results: Sunday, April 25
Why did we Start the Atila TSP?
Back in November 2020, while reading applications for the Atila STEM scholarship we noticed that two finalists were both very interested in medical physics.
Fast forward to March 2021 and it happened again.
While reading the applications for the Atila Olumide and Aramide Ademidun Scholarship. We asked students, ‚Äútalk about a time you overcame adversity‚Äù and ‚Äúwhat are your plans for the future?‚Äù:
Multiple students talked about them or their parents having cancer and students interested in Cancer research.
Many students mentioned they are interested in clean energy and carbon capture.
There are a lot more stories exactly like this.
So we thought to ourselves, ‚ÄúIt would be awesome if there was a community for these students to meet and work with each other.‚Äù So we made one and called it the Atila Top Scholar Program.
What does an Atila Top Scholar Do?
Connect and network
b
with other students working on ideas and projects that you are also interested in. Atila will also connect you with people and resources to help with your idea and project.
Learn useful skills
b
. Learn practical, intangible skills for your education, career and life that you won‚Äôt learn in school.
Make some money.
b
A lot of you are full-time students or doing co-op or internships. We have some opportunities for flexible ways for you to make some money on the side while keeping your other obligations.
Give us feedback.
b
Atila was made to help students. We want to know, ‚Äúhow can we make Atila better for students?‚Äù Help us help you.

The Atila TSP is completely free. The benefit for us is being able to directly engage with and learn from the top students on the Atila platform about how we can make Atila better and hopefully have you tell others about Atila.
How do I become an Atila Top Scholar?

the Wiki page

The Atila team reviews your application and will get back to you in 2-3 weeks
What types of students does Atila look for?

Atila is looking for students who take initiative. We want to see what activities and opportunities you've done beyond just g classroom. We're also looking at a variety of student types from engineering students, computer science, to business to creative arts students.
The Atila TSP application is a chance for us to learn more about you and your interests. We ask the following questions:
What is something that you've done that you're proud of?

Here's some ideas: a research project, a video you made, app you've built, a business you started (entrepreneurship), raising money or volunteering for a good cause, a piece of art, growing a social media account on Instagram/TikTok etc. Literally anything!
If you could take a year off school and do anything, what would you do and why?
If you had a million dollars to invest, what would you do with the money?
We don't mean stocks. Think bigger. It can be an idea, a social movement, an emerging technology, it can even be a person. Anything goes, be creative.
Finally, if you know someone else who would be a great fit for the program. Invite them!

We have a private Slack channel for members of the Atila TSP so they can connect with each other, get early access to new Atila features and directly communicate with us for things we can do to improve Atila.

Like we mentioned a lot of you are doing very cool things and we believe that people doing cool things should meet each other. I went to one of the best business schools in the country, (not just a flex, I‚Äôm actually going somewhere with this)¬† the single best thing I got from going to one of the top universities was meeting other really smart people that motivated me a lot. I think when you‚Äôre young and ambitious it‚Äôs rare to come across people that are equally ambitious as you. We realized that we‚Äôve already identified such people through our platform and we think you folks should meet each other.
We can also help each other out, if you know someone that is looking to hire, we can set up a jobs channel where people can post if they are looking for internships, resume review etc.

Sometimes we do cool stuff, but it can be hard showing your cool stuff, so we will give people an opportunity to talk about the cool stuff they‚Äôve worked on. However, sometimes it‚Äôs good to share what you‚Äôve worked on with the world. We want to create a safe space for people to share their work and then connect with each other. For example, two of our STEM finalists are doing research in biophysics and it would be cool if they got connected with each other. For a fun challenge, i won‚Äôt say who it is but I‚Äôm curious to see if they can find each other.

Due to the pandemic, we obviously can‚Äôt physically meet each other right now but if all goes well we plan on doing social activities to get to know each other as soon as it's safe to do so. For example, it might be cool to have everyone meet up for a dinner in Toronto, paid for by Atila, where everyone can hang out, get to know each other, enjoy some free food etc. We‚Äôll try to find a way to do something for people outside of GTA since we have a very distributed program. We can also do virtual socials in the interim.
As an Atila TSP you will get early or exclusive access to different events that would be useful to members of the Atila team.
Practical workshops from the Atila team on things that we think you will find useful or topics you ask us to talk about.
How to get an internship using Twitter, Instagram and LinkedIn
The two most important digital skills to learn: coding and content creation
How to make friends in a new environment
We‚Äôve had some very incredible people come and talk on our podcast. Get an opportunity to hear from them directly. Some of them may also be able to offer direct internship referrals.

We will also directly connect you with internship and fulltime opportunities at some of the top companies that are hiring. If you are interested in research or grad school, we can connect you with top professors and research institutions.

One of the applicants to the Atila STEM scholarship had an extremely strong application and talked about her work in the biotech space. I have a contact at Andressen Horowitz's Bio Fund. So I gave her the opportunity to connect with them.

In addition to the prizes mentioned in the blog post, there will also be additional prizes for the students in the Atila Top Scholar program with the most points. So yes, it‚Äôs possible for a student to win a prize for both the general student audience and the Atila Top Scholar group.
Alternatively, if the Atila Top Scholar did not finish in the top 5 for the Atila wide rankings. They could still win an award.
How to Get Students and Sponsors

One of the core things we talk about is: First, learn, second, give value, third, sell. So this means that don‚Äôt just go everywhere spamming your invite links. Instead, be thoughtful about who would benefit the most from signing up for Atila.

For example, if you ask your guidance counsellor if you can give a presentation on scholarships. Don‚Äôt make it a sales pitch for Atila, even though you might think we would like that. No one likes being sold to. Instead focus on learning what the kids in your class want to do after school, give them value by offering lots of great advice, you can even mention other websites, then you can talk about why Atila is awesome and how they can use your link. We usually like to slip in the plug somewhere in the middle so that it‚Äôs not obtrusive enough to be annoying, but it‚Äôs enough to get the point across.

Companies you‚Äôve worked for or currently work for
How to NOT Get Students or Sponsors

At Atila one of our values is ‚Äúbet on people, not rules‚Äù. So while we have some rules in place, we try to only work with people that we think have high integrity and trust them to use their judgement, we find that this works better than having 100s of rules in place.
With that being said here are some things that you should NOT be doing and doing so may result in you being removed from the TSP program and banned from the Atila site.
Don‚Äôt do anything spammy or annoying. Follow the
golden rule

We have a two strike policy on complaints from others. If someone complains to us about how they were approached it will be one strike. If they complain again, you will be removed from the program.
Me or someone on the team has interacted with you so we don‚Äôt think that will happen but it‚Äôs just something for you to be aware of.
Ask Questions and Share your Thoughts
We provide lots of avenues for you to get in touch with any of us so we want to hear from you.
We Want to Hear from You

This is the first time we are launching the program so we are still learning, changing things and iterating. We are still working things out so anything here is subject to change at any time. For example, we may decide to do top 5 students instead of top 3 or increase the max points per scholarship to 2,000 or any other list of such changes (don‚Äôt worry it will make sense as we go on). So please let us know if there are any suggestions.
Is the Top Scholar Program a good name? Is the Atila points system and rewards policy fair etc? One of the
